{
  "texts": [
    "The reported CNNs were quite similar, consisting of a mixture of two to four convolutional layers, each followed by a mixture of ReLu, Dropout, and Max Pooling functions, then fully connected layers before the final activation function.",
    "The only exceptions were Atyabi et al. (2023), who used 32 convolutional layers, and Liaqat et al. (2021), who used a pre-trained ResNet-18 (He et al., 2015).",
    "The VTNet from Sims and Conati (2020) was also interesting because they combined a CNN that processed scanpath images in parallel to a GRU that processed the raw gaze data.",
    "The 2-layer CNN and the 1-layer GRU with 256 units were combined afterwards using two fully connected layers and a Softmax activation.",
    "The reported MLPs were not often provided with a lot of details."
  ]
}